BT 1 0 0 1 0 58 Tm /F1 10 Tf 17 TL -0.018696 Tw (The classical figure is 7.5 to 8 heads tall. The width of the shoulders is about 2 heads wide. The waist sits at 3) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.100952 Tw (heads down, the hips at 4, the knees at 6. These are starting points \227 not rules. Every body deviates from the) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.32625 Tw (canon, and those deviations define the individual. Learn the standard first, then learn to see where reality) Tj T* 0 Tw (differs.) Tj T* ET
