BT 1 0 0 1 0 58 Tm .213158 Tw 17 TL /F1 10 Tf .941176 .921569 .890196 rg (The most important proportion in portraiture: the eyes sit at the ) Tj /F2 10 Tf (midpoint of the head) Tj /F1 10 Tf (, not near the top. Most) Tj T* 0 Tw .268947 Tw (beginners draw eyes too high. The nose is halfway between the eyes and the chin. The mouth is one-third of) Tj T* 0 Tw .388421 Tw (the way from nose to chin. The ears align from eye level to nose level. These relationships hold across most) Tj T* 0 Tw (faces, regardless of age, gender, or ethnicity.) Tj T* ET
